```java
f.setVisible(true);
```
This should be the last line in the `Sudokuu` constructor.
```java
f.add(p);
```
This means you are adding `p` to the center of `f`. You wrote in your question that `p` should appear above the Sudoku board (which is `field` in your code). Hence you should chenge the above line to:
```java
f.add(p, BorderLayout.PAGE_START);
```
You are also adding `p` to `field`.
```java
field.add(p);
```
You need to remove this line.
```java
field.setLayout(new GridLayout(9, 9));
```
For [GridLayout](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/layout/grid.html) you only need to set one dimension, so replace the above line with:
```java
field.setLayout(new GridLayout(0, 9));
```
This ensures that there will be, at most, nine columns in each row of the grid.
```java
f.setLayout(new BorderLayout());
```
This is not required as `BorderLayout` is the default.
```java
field.setVisible(true);
```
This is not required since *visible* is true by default.
```java
f.add(field, BorderLayout.CENTER);
```
Add `field` to `f` **after** you have added all the components to `field`.
```java
p.setSize(700, 50);
```
I think it is more correct to set the preferred size, i.e.
```java
p.setPreferredSize(new Dimension(700, 50));
```

